WEBVTT

00:06.093 --> 00:08.312
Alright, Bill,
see ya.

00:08.486 --> 00:09.487
Later, buddy.Have a great weekend.

00:09.661 --> 00:10.967
What?

00:11.141 --> 00:12.664
Have a great week--

00:12.838 --> 00:14.710
Wait, hold on.
It's -- It's Friday?

00:14.884 --> 00:16.190
Yeeeeeah.

00:16.364 --> 00:17.713
[ Chuckles ]

00:17.887 --> 00:19.280
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

00:19.454 --> 00:20.455
This can't be.

00:20.629 --> 00:21.847
But...why not?

00:22.022 --> 00:24.241
You don't have kids.

00:24.415 --> 00:26.852
When there's
no school...

00:27.027 --> 00:28.550
there's no childcare.

00:28.724 --> 00:30.247
Bummer.

00:30.421 --> 00:31.596
You don't understand!

00:31.770 --> 00:33.468
The weekend is worse
than the week!

00:33.642 --> 00:35.383
Is someone filming this?!
Human resources?!

00:35.557 --> 00:37.298
Ken!

00:37.472 --> 00:40.866
No, no, please,
just give me more work!

00:41.041 --> 00:43.434
Aah!
I want to stay here!

00:43.608 --> 00:45.741
The weekend is worse
than the week!

00:45.915 --> 00:48.004
It's worse than the week!

00:48.178 --> 00:50.833
It's worse than the week!

00:51.007 --> 00:52.269
It's worse than the week!

00:52.443 --> 00:54.054
Bill, Bill! Bill!Eh? Ah! Uh! Ah!

00:54.228 --> 00:56.360
Bill!
Oh!

00:56.534 --> 00:58.841
Oh, man, I just had a nightmare
it was the weekend.

00:59.015 --> 00:59.885
It isSaturday.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.278
[ Groans ]

01:01.452 --> 01:04.281
So, I didn't scream
at my office?

01:04.455 --> 01:05.848
I don't know.

01:06.022 --> 01:07.676
We'll find out Monday,
I guess.

01:07.850 --> 01:08.459
[ Grunts ]
[ Groans ]

01:08.633 --> 01:10.287
God.

01:10.461 --> 01:11.419
[ Sighs ]

01:11.593 --> 01:13.116
Remember how
weekends used to be?

01:13.290 --> 01:14.552
Sleep till noon.

01:14.726 --> 01:16.685
Yeah, take off
on my motorcycle.

01:16.859 --> 01:18.208
Poop alone.

01:18.382 --> 01:20.167
Well,
all that's gone.

01:20.341 --> 01:21.646
Now it's just kid stuff
and family obligations.

01:21.820 --> 01:22.821
Mm.

01:22.995 --> 01:24.345
Ooh, and this weekend,

01:24.519 --> 01:27.391
Emily has her first
homework assignment.

01:27.565 --> 01:29.524
Come on.
Emily has homework now?

01:29.698 --> 01:31.439
Just for
the next 12 years.

01:31.613 --> 01:34.355
[ Chuckles ]
Happy Saturday.

01:34.529 --> 01:35.660
Ohh.

01:35.834 --> 01:37.923
Hey.

01:38.098 --> 01:41.231
The kids are still asleep.
So...

01:41.405 --> 01:44.321
Mm. You want to have
nervous, silent sex while
we stare at the door?

01:46.541 --> 01:51.111
[ Both chanting "Pancakes!" ]

01:54.288 --> 02:03.210
♪♪♪

02:04.863 --> 02:06.343
We want waffles.

02:08.215 --> 02:09.607
And we're off.

02:12.175 --> 02:14.134
Mmm.
Toothpaste and coffee.

02:14.308 --> 02:15.135
The working man's
peppermint latte.

02:17.659 --> 02:19.269
What's the damage today,
Jo?

02:19.443 --> 02:21.445
[ Sighs ] We've got
two kids' birthday parties.

02:21.619 --> 02:23.012
Actual friends,
fake school friends,

02:23.186 --> 02:24.144
family,
or people we hate?

02:26.537 --> 02:28.148
Combo move.

02:28.322 --> 02:29.497
Lulu's friend
and my brother Benicio's kid.

02:31.107 --> 02:32.674
Do we have to go
to the Benicio thing?

02:34.328 --> 02:36.721
Do you know how annoying
he'll be if we don't go?

02:36.895 --> 02:39.071
As annoying
as if we do go?

02:39.246 --> 02:40.290
And we have a funeral.

02:40.464 --> 02:41.813
Oh, God!

02:41.987 --> 02:43.641
Your family
constantly dies.

02:43.815 --> 02:45.295
Who is it this time?

02:46.905 --> 02:49.212
My cousin Luis.
The guy with all the turtles.

02:49.386 --> 02:50.866
Enh.
They were tortoises.

02:51.040 --> 02:52.737
Well, whatever they were,
he died,

02:52.911 --> 02:53.477
and they ate his toes.

02:55.044 --> 02:55.914
Hey. I hope
you do that to me.

02:56.088 --> 02:58.047
[ Chuckles ]

02:58.221 --> 03:00.528
At least both birthdays
are at Party Pizza,

03:00.702 --> 03:02.573
so, you know, we won't be stuck
in the car with the kids.

03:02.747 --> 03:04.445
Oh, thank God.

03:04.619 --> 03:05.794
Oh. Wait.

03:05.968 --> 03:07.578
No. Sorry.

03:07.752 --> 03:09.363
They're at two different
Party Pizzas --

03:09.537 --> 03:10.799
40 miles apart?!

03:10.973 --> 03:12.409
What the...

03:12.583 --> 03:14.150
Aren't weekends relaxing?

03:14.324 --> 03:15.804
Ugh.
Boy, do I need it.

03:15.978 --> 03:17.414
[ Laughs ]

03:17.588 --> 03:18.415
Why?
What'd you do all week?

03:18.589 --> 03:19.938
Bought pantyhose,

03:20.112 --> 03:21.679
saw the dentist,

03:21.853 --> 03:23.115
mailed a letter.

03:25.161 --> 03:26.815
I don't know how
I got it all done.

03:26.989 --> 03:28.382
[ Slurps ]

03:28.556 --> 03:29.818
Ahh.

03:29.992 --> 03:30.906
Ooh, that's good joe.

03:32.429 --> 03:33.343
[ Slurps ]

03:35.127 --> 03:37.434
Ahhhhh.

03:37.608 --> 03:39.044
Tell you what --
let's just drive aimlessly

03:39.219 --> 03:40.307
until that first party
starts.
Yeah.

03:41.960 --> 03:44.006
Oh, look.
They're opening our gift.

03:44.180 --> 03:46.704
I grabbed something Lulu
never opened on herbirthday.

03:46.878 --> 03:47.966
It's the perfect crime.

03:48.140 --> 03:50.491
Aw, look!

03:50.665 --> 03:52.797
"To Lulu.
Happy Birthday.

03:52.971 --> 03:54.321
Love, Daphne."

03:57.802 --> 03:58.629
Since
you already hate us,

03:58.803 --> 03:59.978
we're gonna take a pizza
for the car.

04:00.152 --> 04:03.243
♪♪♪

04:03.417 --> 04:05.157
[ Noisemaker honking ]

04:09.597 --> 04:11.251
Thank you.

04:11.425 --> 04:12.513
I mean, what are we doing
with our lives, huh?

04:12.687 --> 04:13.775
We work all week
so we can do all this?

04:13.949 --> 04:15.080
Yes.

04:15.255 --> 04:16.517
You wanted to have kids.

04:16.691 --> 04:19.302
Uh, no, I didn't.
Youdid.

04:19.476 --> 04:22.610
Well, I guess there's been
a huge miscommunication.

04:22.784 --> 04:25.613
Come on, babe, why do we have to
go to allyour family events?

04:25.787 --> 04:28.398
Because otherwise,
we're not a family.

04:28.572 --> 04:30.052
We're just a bunch of people
in the same city

04:30.226 --> 04:32.272
with the same nose.

04:32.446 --> 04:35.840
All I wanted to do today was
watch the U. Colorado game.

04:36.014 --> 04:37.102
You can do that.

04:37.277 --> 04:40.280
Jo,
we made one promise.

04:40.454 --> 04:42.282
To never lie
to each other, okay?

04:42.456 --> 04:44.675
Please do not violate
that sacred covenant now,

04:44.849 --> 04:46.547
or we...have nothing.

04:46.721 --> 04:47.548
[ Chuckles ]

04:49.506 --> 04:50.986
What if this weekend,

04:51.160 --> 04:54.381
we each got to do one
small thing for ourselves?

04:54.555 --> 04:55.730
Totally depends.
What's yours?

04:55.904 --> 04:57.819
I'd like to
get my nails done.

04:57.993 --> 04:59.864
My feet look like
a Johnny Depp necklace.

05:00.038 --> 05:02.214
Deal. Game today.
Nails on Sunday.

05:02.389 --> 05:03.215
Whoo-hoo!

05:03.390 --> 05:04.565
[ Noisemaker honks ]

05:07.350 --> 05:09.439
Okay,
Benicio is depressing,

05:09.613 --> 05:12.573
so don't encourage it
for your own amusement.

05:12.747 --> 05:14.966
Ah, come on. That's the only joy
I can get out of the guy.

05:15.140 --> 05:18.840
I've met him, like, 300 times.
He never remembers who I am.

05:19.014 --> 05:20.189
Nine siblings,
and you're the only one

05:20.363 --> 05:22.278
who showed for
my son's birthday.

05:22.452 --> 05:23.323
Typical.

05:25.499 --> 05:28.153
Benicio, I-I'm sure Chuy
just has our other brothers

05:28.328 --> 05:29.981
helping out
at Luis' funeral.

05:30.155 --> 05:31.461
You know how he is.[ Scoffs ]

05:31.635 --> 05:33.637
Oh, I know how he is.

05:33.811 --> 05:34.986
You know Chuy stole my life,
right?

05:35.160 --> 05:36.640
Yes.
No. How?

05:38.729 --> 05:40.775
September 10, 2001.

05:40.949 --> 05:42.907
Oh, boy.

05:43.081 --> 05:45.214
I spot Brie Gonzalez
at the school dance,

05:45.388 --> 05:49.479
and I turn to my brother Chuy,
and I say, "Dibs."

05:52.221 --> 05:54.266
The next thing you know,
they're married and have kids,

05:54.441 --> 05:56.486
like I never had dibs.

05:56.660 --> 05:58.401
That's crazy.

05:58.575 --> 06:00.577
I should be living in his house
with his family,

06:00.751 --> 06:02.231
and he should be the one

06:02.405 --> 06:04.712
whose air mattress exploded
last night.

06:04.886 --> 06:06.583
You can't call dibs
on a person.

06:06.757 --> 06:08.063
I think you can,
you know?

06:08.237 --> 06:10.935
I-I'm on your side.

06:11.109 --> 06:14.330
It may be Luis' funeral,
but it is Chuy who's dead to me.

06:14.504 --> 06:15.462
Forever.

06:16.724 --> 06:18.769
My sister's so rude.

06:18.943 --> 06:20.292
I'm Benicio,
by the way.

06:21.816 --> 06:23.470
I'm...also Benicio.

06:27.561 --> 06:28.866
[ Organ music plays ]

06:34.916 --> 06:36.439
You're the only family
who showed.

06:36.613 --> 06:37.962
[ Sighs ]
Well, of course.

06:38.136 --> 06:39.616
I show up to everything.
[ Scoffs ]

06:39.790 --> 06:41.401
Where are
the other brothers?

06:41.575 --> 06:43.490
I don't know. We just saw
Benicio at his kid's birthday.

06:43.664 --> 06:46.493
Hey, Benicio isn't still
talking about dibs, is he?

06:47.929 --> 06:49.409
[ Chuckling ]
Yeah, he was.

06:49.583 --> 06:50.671
You know how he is.

06:50.845 --> 06:52.716
Uh, yeah.
I know how he is.

06:54.631 --> 06:56.633
Well, time to go
crush this funeral.

06:59.070 --> 07:00.768
The game starts
in an hour.

07:00.942 --> 07:02.683
Don't worry, babe.
We'll sit in the back.

07:02.857 --> 07:03.988
If it goes too long,
we'll sneak out.
Okay, okay.

07:04.162 --> 07:05.816
Bill! Jo!

07:05.990 --> 07:08.297
There's seats up front!
Get over here!

07:08.471 --> 07:11.518
Look at this whole row!
Come with me!

07:11.692 --> 07:14.259
Okay, look,
Chuy barely knew Luis.

07:14.434 --> 07:15.565
This'll be 10 minutes,
tops.
Okay.

07:17.393 --> 07:19.700
First, I'd like to thank
the tortoise community

07:19.874 --> 07:21.441
for your incredible support.

07:23.965 --> 07:26.010
What can you say
about Luis?

07:26.184 --> 07:26.924
Nothing.

07:27.098 --> 07:28.839
Good.

07:29.013 --> 07:30.711
But what can I say
about Luis?

07:30.885 --> 07:32.800
A whole buttload of stuff.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.628
Bad.

07:34.802 --> 07:37.326
Luis loved baseball.

07:37.500 --> 07:40.024
He watched
every Rockies game.

07:40.198 --> 07:42.723
162 a year!

07:45.334 --> 07:46.944
In his honor,

07:47.118 --> 07:50.774
we will now take
162 moments of silence.

07:55.083 --> 07:57.085
One...

07:57.259 --> 07:58.869
Game starts
in five minutes.

07:59.043 --> 08:00.654
Oh,
just start recording it.

08:00.828 --> 08:01.829
Two...

08:03.439 --> 08:04.658
101...

08:06.573 --> 08:08.226
Why did Luis love tortoises?

08:08.400 --> 08:10.228
Who cares?

08:10.402 --> 08:12.970
They're so slow,

08:13.144 --> 08:16.191
and everyone hates
when things go slow.

08:16.365 --> 08:18.193
Yeah, amen.

08:18.367 --> 08:20.761
What's the rush?
Hmm?

08:20.935 --> 08:22.414
Everyone's in a hurry
to get somewhere

08:22.589 --> 08:24.634
better than where they are.

08:24.808 --> 08:26.636
And all these things
that we rush past...

08:30.031 --> 08:32.207
...well, that's life.

08:32.381 --> 08:33.382
Slow down!

08:35.602 --> 08:38.082
Enjoy your life!

08:38.256 --> 08:40.650
Live.

08:40.824 --> 08:41.999
Like.

08:42.173 --> 08:45.002
A.

08:45.176 --> 08:46.395
Tortoise.

08:49.311 --> 08:51.879
[ Voice breaking ]
He always gets me at the end.

08:52.053 --> 08:53.402
Thank you, Denver!
Good night!

08:55.317 --> 08:56.884
Okay, look,
I-I got to get out of here

08:57.058 --> 08:58.363
before someone
tells me the score.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.800
I'll just see you at the car,
okay?
Okay.

08:59.974 --> 09:03.368
♪♪♪

09:03.543 --> 09:04.892
Bill,
did you see the game?!

09:05.066 --> 09:06.763
No, Mo-- Shh, shh, shh.
I recorded it.

09:06.937 --> 09:08.548
Wait, where is it?[ Beeping ]

09:08.722 --> 09:10.593
Oh, it asked if
I wanted to record it,

09:10.767 --> 09:12.595
but I didn't see any
reason, 'cause I was
already watching it.

09:15.467 --> 09:17.774
[ Cheering]Announcer:
And there you have it!

09:17.948 --> 09:21.125
The greatest comeback victory
in Colorado history!

09:21.299 --> 09:23.911
I feel bad for anyone
who missed it!

09:29.612 --> 09:31.309
Please don't touch the remote.
I'm recording something.

09:31.483 --> 09:33.137
♪♪♪

09:36.401 --> 09:38.708
It's worse than the week!
It's worse than the week!

09:38.882 --> 09:39.404
It's worse
than the week!

09:39.579 --> 09:41.189
Bill!
Eh! Ah! Ah!

09:41.363 --> 09:42.973
Oh, no.

09:43.147 --> 09:44.366
I just had a nightmare
it's --

09:44.540 --> 09:45.715
It isSunday.

09:48.109 --> 09:50.198
The kids are still asleep,
so...

09:50.372 --> 09:52.635
Oh.

09:52.809 --> 09:55.333
[ Both chanting "Waffles!" ]

09:55.507 --> 10:00.034
♪♪♪

10:00.208 --> 10:01.122
Let me guess.
You want pancakes?

10:01.296 --> 10:02.863
No. Cereal.

10:07.389 --> 10:08.738
[ Sighs ]

10:08.912 --> 10:10.348
So, JoJo, Sunday plans.
What do you got?

10:10.522 --> 10:12.133
Uh, there's...

10:13.787 --> 10:14.744
...nothing.

10:17.355 --> 10:20.402
No parties,
nothing with my family.

10:20.576 --> 10:22.186
Oh, my God.

10:22.360 --> 10:25.233
I have dreamed of this day
for so long.

10:25.407 --> 10:28.105
I know.

10:28.279 --> 10:30.542
Now that it's here, I have
no idea what to do with it.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.240
Ooh, I have an idea --

10:32.414 --> 10:33.154
nothing.

10:34.416 --> 10:35.460
Just relax.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.245
Oh, yes.
Right?

10:37.419 --> 10:39.900
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Just stay home and relax.

10:40.074 --> 10:41.553
Oh, my gosh.
That actually sounds amazing.

10:41.728 --> 10:42.685
[ Chuckles ]

10:42.859 --> 10:43.773
[ Sighs ]

10:43.947 --> 10:45.557
[ Bell dinging ]

10:45.732 --> 10:47.255
Bang! Bang! Bang!
Whap! Bang!

10:47.429 --> 10:49.344
Ahhhh!

10:49.518 --> 10:50.650
We got to
get out of here.

10:52.521 --> 10:53.435
What can we do?

10:53.609 --> 10:55.916
And don't say...

10:56.090 --> 10:57.308
or they will
make us do it.

10:57.482 --> 10:58.658
A movie?

10:58.832 --> 11:01.573
Movie!
We're going to a movie!

11:01.748 --> 11:03.184
Oopsie doodle.

11:05.012 --> 11:06.361
Fine, we'll take you
to a movie,

11:06.535 --> 11:08.102
but then you have to
do your homework tonight.

11:08.276 --> 11:11.366
Yay!
I'll get my jacket!

11:11.540 --> 11:13.585
Okay, look, babe,
after the movie,

11:13.760 --> 11:14.674
I'll take the kids
to the food court,

11:14.848 --> 11:16.110
and you can
get your nails done.

11:16.284 --> 11:18.678
And then a bottle of wine
and oblivion.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.769
Can't wait for that.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.163
I literally
can't wait for that.

11:26.337 --> 11:28.818
I'm gonna make that happen
right now.

11:28.992 --> 11:32.039
Okay, you get the car,
I'll get the kids, okay?

11:32.213 --> 11:33.649
Kids! Come on!
Let's go!

11:33.823 --> 11:37.522
Emily:
I can't find my jacket!

11:37.697 --> 11:39.133
Emily's jacket.

11:39.307 --> 11:42.266
You left it at the funeral
yesterday.

11:42.440 --> 11:44.051
Thank you, but we --
we really got to go.

11:44.225 --> 11:45.400
Oh, I'll be brief.
Please, come in.

11:45.574 --> 11:46.140
[ Door closes ]

11:49.186 --> 11:52.276
I-I can't stop thinking
about what God said yesterday.

11:52.450 --> 11:53.843
When He spoke through me
at Luis' funeral.

11:55.584 --> 11:57.107
Chuy,
we're really in a hurry.

11:57.281 --> 11:58.848
Well,
when God and I said that

11:59.022 --> 12:01.155
everyone is in way too much
of a hurry...

12:01.329 --> 12:02.504
Okay, yeah, but we actually
arein a hurry, okay?

12:02.678 --> 12:03.461
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:06.116 --> 12:07.509
Lulu's jacket.

12:07.683 --> 12:08.945
You left it
at Jose's party.

12:09.119 --> 12:10.512
Thank you, Beni.

12:10.686 --> 12:12.514
Uh, kids,
we got to get out of here!

12:12.688 --> 12:14.690
That's okay.
I've got a minute.

12:14.864 --> 12:16.779
Brother.

12:16.953 --> 12:19.216
Once upon a time.

12:19.390 --> 12:21.392
I see what you did, Jo.

12:21.566 --> 12:23.307
You left one jacket at
the funeral and the other at...

12:23.481 --> 12:25.614
At Jose's party, knowing
we would each feel compelled

12:25.788 --> 12:26.876
to return the jacket...

12:27.050 --> 12:27.964
And settle the feud

12:28.138 --> 12:30.227
between us.
Between us.

12:30.401 --> 12:32.186
Right. Yeah.

12:32.360 --> 12:33.535
'Cause we're not just
two stressed-out people

12:33.709 --> 12:36.668
with kids leaving crap
everywhere we go.

12:36.843 --> 12:39.323
This ends right here,
right now.

12:39.497 --> 12:41.238
Hey, do you guys maybe want to
do this at a Starbucks?

12:41.412 --> 12:41.891
'Cause...

12:52.772 --> 12:53.816
Hey,
aren't you worried?

12:53.990 --> 12:55.252
No. I hope
they kill each other.

12:57.298 --> 13:00.170
Alright, we made it,
with three minutes to spare.

13:00.344 --> 13:02.825
Ha! For once, our family
didn't blow up our lives.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.087
Uh-oh.

13:04.261 --> 13:04.784
What?

13:08.788 --> 13:10.615
[ Scoffs ]

13:10.790 --> 13:12.443
My God.

13:12.617 --> 13:13.575
I mean,
we can't wake them.

13:13.749 --> 13:15.185
No way.

13:15.359 --> 13:17.971
They'll turn into demons.

13:18.145 --> 13:19.842
Bye, movie.

13:20.016 --> 13:21.931
Bye, $50.

13:22.105 --> 13:25.500
You know, I swear,
they're messing with us.

13:25.674 --> 13:26.806
[ Scoffs ]

13:26.980 --> 13:29.199
Another weekend disaster.

13:29.373 --> 13:30.940
Ohh.
No, come on, babe.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.681
Look, I missed my game,

13:32.855 --> 13:33.725
but you can still
go get your nails done.

13:33.900 --> 13:35.858
I can't leave you alone.

13:36.032 --> 13:37.599
You have to.

13:38.730 --> 13:39.557
I can't.

13:39.731 --> 13:41.516
Eh...

13:41.690 --> 13:43.735
I'm already dead.
It's too late for me.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.302
But you can still live.

13:45.476 --> 13:47.914
Go.
Get your nails done.

13:49.132 --> 13:50.220
What if they wake up?

13:50.394 --> 13:52.092
They will.

13:52.266 --> 13:54.616
Now...go,
before theydo.

13:58.925 --> 14:00.100
[ Strained ]
Remember me!

14:20.990 --> 14:21.556
They're closed.

14:21.730 --> 14:22.600
Oh.

14:22.774 --> 14:23.775
♪♪♪

14:26.866 --> 14:28.302
[ Sighs ] God.

14:28.476 --> 14:30.521
What are we about to
walk into here?

14:30.695 --> 14:32.001
[ Both sobbing ]

14:37.528 --> 14:38.965
Damn it.
Everyone's still alive.

14:42.490 --> 14:44.840
The feud that has
destroyed this family

14:45.014 --> 14:46.015
is at last resolved.

14:48.322 --> 14:50.019
We finally realized
what the problem was.

14:50.193 --> 14:51.673
Great.
What was it?

14:51.847 --> 14:53.109
You.

14:54.545 --> 14:56.460
What are you
talking about?

14:56.634 --> 14:59.768
Jo, you stoked the flames
of this feud.

14:59.942 --> 15:01.509
You pitted us against
each other,

15:01.683 --> 15:04.381
like a demon
puppet-master.

15:04.555 --> 15:05.861
That's insane.

15:06.035 --> 15:07.907
Is it, Jo?

15:08.081 --> 15:09.952
Yesterday, when I asked you
if Chuy was mad at me,

15:10.126 --> 15:12.476
you said,
"You know how he is."

15:12.650 --> 15:14.696
And when I asked you
if Benicio was mad at me,

15:14.870 --> 15:16.698
you said,
"You know how he is."

15:16.872 --> 15:18.482
So?

15:18.656 --> 15:20.441
How am I, Jo?

15:20.615 --> 15:22.138
And how am I?

15:23.835 --> 15:25.272
Like this!

15:27.056 --> 15:29.015
Well, we disagree.

15:29.189 --> 15:30.407
You'rethe one who is.

15:30.581 --> 15:32.148
And who continues
to be "is."

15:34.150 --> 15:35.760
Me?
[ Scoffs ]

15:35.935 --> 15:38.546
I am the one who holds
this whole family together.

15:38.720 --> 15:40.069
Listen, guys,
we're the only ones

15:40.243 --> 15:42.637
who go to every party
and funeral.

15:42.811 --> 15:45.161
I mean, Jo is the glue
of your family.

15:45.335 --> 15:47.207
And you actually think
I'm the problem?

15:47.381 --> 15:49.122
Yes,
that's what we just said.

15:50.732 --> 15:51.733
[ Chuckles ]

15:51.907 --> 15:53.387
Sure.

15:53.561 --> 15:55.128
Hey, whatever helps you
sleep at night.

15:55.302 --> 15:56.607
1,000 burpees.

15:56.781 --> 15:58.522
Children's Benadryl
and vermouth.

16:02.352 --> 16:06.791
Chuy Marco
Alejandro Rodriguez,

16:06.966 --> 16:09.011
I release the dibs.

16:10.795 --> 16:13.320
Benicio Alejandro
Marco Rodriguez,

16:13.494 --> 16:14.756
I thank you.

16:14.930 --> 16:15.975
We're brothers again.

16:20.675 --> 16:23.721
And, Sandy, you are
a miracle worker.

16:26.420 --> 16:28.248
W-What did she do?

16:30.815 --> 16:35.081
I told them you can't
call dibs on a person.

16:38.954 --> 16:39.999
Well,
I think you can.

16:41.957 --> 16:43.828
Let's all go out
and celebrate!

16:44.003 --> 16:46.440
Oh!
I'm buying, boys.[ Laughs ]

16:46.614 --> 16:47.615
Okay, we'd love to,
but we can't.

16:47.789 --> 16:48.703
We got the kids.

16:48.877 --> 16:50.487
Too bad!
Come on, fellas.

16:52.663 --> 16:54.926
You know, you really got to
learn to enjoy the weekend, man.

16:55.101 --> 16:56.276
By the way,
I'm Benicio.

16:58.234 --> 17:00.019
Well, we did it.

17:00.193 --> 17:01.933
Another weekend
in the books.

17:02.108 --> 17:04.414
No,
we didn't do it.

17:04.588 --> 17:07.069
Emily's homework,
remember?

17:07.243 --> 17:09.115
Unbelievable.

17:09.289 --> 17:12.509
Every time we feel like
we're done, we're not done.

17:12.683 --> 17:14.337
Emily, let's go.

17:14.511 --> 17:16.209
Why can't I just play
with Play-Doh?

17:16.383 --> 17:17.558
It's in the name.

17:19.473 --> 17:22.041
Because you can't just
do whatever you want
every second, sweetie.

17:22.215 --> 17:23.738
Youdo
whatever youwant.

17:23.912 --> 17:25.957
[ Scoffs ]

17:26.132 --> 17:27.742
What?!

17:27.916 --> 17:29.831
Your dad wanted to
watch the game.

17:30.005 --> 17:31.659
I wanted to
get my nails done.

17:31.833 --> 17:34.227
We didn't get to do anything
we wanted to do this weekend.

17:34.401 --> 17:36.055
Well,
I want ice cream.

17:36.229 --> 17:38.405
No.
Do your homework.

17:38.579 --> 17:39.667
I'll do it
if you give me ice cream.

17:39.841 --> 17:41.669
No ice cream!

17:41.843 --> 17:44.106
Okay? Go!
Do your homework! Now!

17:44.280 --> 17:46.195
You're so mean!
I hate you, Mom!

17:49.720 --> 17:50.939
[ Sighs ]

17:51.113 --> 17:52.854
Wow, that was
an emotional hit job.

17:53.028 --> 17:54.421
Alright.

17:54.595 --> 17:55.726
Look,
she doesn't hate you.

17:55.900 --> 17:56.901
I know, but still.

17:57.076 --> 17:58.860
Gosh.

17:59.034 --> 18:01.732
Why are, like, the simplest
things so hard?

18:01.906 --> 18:03.169
Yeah, I can't wait until
they're out of the house.

18:03.343 --> 18:04.431
We can just sit here,
drinking naked.

18:09.566 --> 18:11.655
Imagine doing
whatever we want again.

18:11.829 --> 18:13.788
I would watch every game.

18:13.962 --> 18:16.791
The whole game.

18:16.965 --> 18:19.141
Any sport.
I don't care.

18:19.315 --> 18:20.664
I would just sleep.

18:20.838 --> 18:22.231
Ooh. Me, too.
I change my answer.

18:22.405 --> 18:24.538
That's a good one.

18:24.712 --> 18:26.931
I can't believe we've sacrificed
all our freedom

18:27.106 --> 18:29.673
just to get screamed at.

18:29.847 --> 18:31.371
Babe, you know who
I'm almost jealous of?

18:31.545 --> 18:32.589
Hmm?
Luis.

18:35.114 --> 18:36.115
He watched every game,
and then he died.

18:39.161 --> 18:41.555
Death is sleep.

18:41.729 --> 18:44.819
Yeah, but only like eight people
showed up to his funeral.

18:44.993 --> 18:47.778
I don't know.
Maybe Chuy was right.

18:47.952 --> 18:49.345
You know,
maybe we should just...

18:49.519 --> 18:52.870
try to enjoy this time
and slow down.

18:54.481 --> 18:56.135
Hey.
You know what?

18:56.309 --> 18:57.745
I bet 30 years from now,

18:57.919 --> 18:59.181
we'd kill
to have a weekend like this.

18:59.355 --> 19:01.052
[ Chuckles ]

19:01.227 --> 19:04.012
Dude, I'm so tired.

19:04.186 --> 19:05.709
Like, I literally don't care
about anything.

19:05.883 --> 19:07.537
Do you?

19:07.711 --> 19:09.670
Nope.

19:09.844 --> 19:12.151
Emily?

19:12.325 --> 19:13.891
Let's have
some ice cream!

19:15.937 --> 19:17.721
Ohh. Mm.

19:17.895 --> 19:20.681
I'm sorry, Mommy.
I love you.

19:20.855 --> 19:22.900
It's just that I get mad
when I don't get what I want.

19:23.074 --> 19:24.598
I know, pumpkin.

19:24.772 --> 19:25.947
Me, too.

19:26.121 --> 19:26.991
Yeah, me, too.

19:27.166 --> 19:28.210
Oop.

19:31.692 --> 19:32.780
I'll do my homework.

19:32.954 --> 19:34.216
Okay.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.568
[ Sighs ]

19:38.742 --> 19:40.483
What lesson
did we just teach?

19:42.093 --> 19:43.573
Who cares? Tomorrow, she's
the school's problem again.

19:43.747 --> 19:45.227
♪♪♪

19:48.752 --> 19:51.451
"My Weekend,
by Emily Ryan.

19:51.625 --> 19:54.541
I went to two parties
and ate six pieces of cake."

19:55.977 --> 19:58.762
"My uncles fought
in my living room.

19:58.936 --> 20:01.069
Plus, my parents don't work
on weekends,

20:01.243 --> 20:03.985
so I got to spend two whole days
with them.

20:04.159 --> 20:07.031
I have the best family."

20:07.206 --> 20:10.034
Ohhhhh!

20:10.209 --> 20:11.993
You see? She has no idea
we're completely inept.

20:12.167 --> 20:12.950
Mm.

20:14.822 --> 20:16.258
What are you doing?

20:16.432 --> 20:17.259
Making the kids' lunches.

20:17.433 --> 20:18.695
Why?

20:18.869 --> 20:20.001
It's Monday.

20:20.175 --> 20:21.263
It's a holiday weekend.

20:23.874 --> 20:25.963
Boy, do I need it.

20:26.137 --> 20:27.226
[ Slurps ]

20:29.358 --> 20:31.273
Ahhhhh.

20:40.935 --> 20:42.241
Excuse me.

20:48.943 --> 20:50.814
[ Slurps ]

20:50.988 --> 20:52.990
Ahhhhhhh.

20:53.164 --> 20:56.472
Jo: Aaaaaaaaaaah!

20:56.646 --> 20:58.039
Uh-oh.

20:58.213 --> 20:59.910
♪♪♪

21:00.084 --> 21:00.998
Yeah!

21:03.087 --> 21:04.567
♪♪♪
